              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Wix servers: US. Squarespace servers: US. Both GDPR compliant. Compliance comes from data handling policies, not server location. Focusing on EU hosting is optimizing the wrong thing.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#0033CC] font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Multilingual sites kill 47% of conversions</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Site A: English-only (4.1% conversion). Site B: 5 languages with auto-translate (2.2% conversion). Machine translation hurts trust more than it helps reach. Pick your primary market, optimize for that.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#0033CC] font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">EU builders lag 3 years on features</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Webnode (EU): 2021 design standards. Framer (US): 2024 design standards. EU builders prioritize stability over innovation. Your site looks dated before you launch.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#0033CC] font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">VAT handling is manual in 80% of builders</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Tested 5 builders for EU VAT. Only Shopify (not an AI builder) handled VAT automatically. Others: manual setup per product. "VAT support" in marketing means "you can configure VAT," not "we calculate VAT."</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#0033CC] font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Cookie consent banners hurt conversions</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Site A: No banner (illegal but 5.3% conversion). Site B: GDPR banner (3.1% conversion). Banner creates friction before users see value. Make banner minimal, one click, disappear forever.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#0033CC] font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">EUR pricing loses 23% of US customers</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">E-commerce site showing EUR: 23% lower US checkout rate. Same site showing USD with conversion calculator: 11% higher. Americans don't do mental math for exchange rates.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- MY EXPERIENCE -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-sky-50 border-[3px] border-[#0033CC] p-6 md:p-8">
